The paper discusses the field of statistical relational learning, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) that aims to unify logic and probability to reason and learn from data. The paper specifically focuses on probabilistic logic programming, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that enables stochastic primitives in logic programming. The paper also discusses inductive logic programming, which is a subfield of natural language processing (cs.CL) that has paved the way for learning meaningful and interpretable symbolic representations from data. The paper deals with continuous probability distributions, which is a subfield of cryptography (cs.CR) that is concerned with the security of continuous data. Finally, the paper discusses the construction of density functions, which is a subfield of control systems (cs.SY) that deals with the analysis and design of systems that behave in a predictable way.
